7. Recommended Minimum Migration Path (No Live Behavior Change)

Phase 0 — Semantic alignment (this audit)
- Document current state vs target state (this report).

Phase 1 — Create StrategyRuntimeInstance domain model
- New src/domain/strategy_runtime_instance.py with the model.
- No service, no API, no PG table yet. Pure domain model with invariants.

Phase 2 — Bridge admission path
- Ensure AdmissionTrialBinding can produce a StrategyRuntimeInstance draft (application layer only).
- Do not change OwnerTrialFlow or OwnerBoundedExecutionService.

Phase 3 — Add semantic IDs to ExecutionIntent
- Add trial_binding_id, strategy_family_version_id, runtime_instance_id as Optional[str] fields to ExecutionIntent.
- These are additive, backward-compatible.

Phase 4 — PG persistence for StrategyRuntimeInstance
- New table. No changes to existing tables.

Phase 5 — Extend FinalGate with runtime context
- Add optional runtime context checks (attempts remaining, budget remaining).
- FinalGate remains backward-compatible: if no runtime instance, falls back to current behavior.

Phase 6 — Wire runtime path to execution
- OwnerBoundedExecutionService (or a new service) can accept a runtime_instance_id instead of authorization_id.
- One-shot path remains available.

Each phase is independently deployable and does not break the existing one-shot execution pipeline.

